Author: Lumbi#8378
Content: @Vertigo takes way more time to heal than you would think (9+ months). a good physical therapist with electro-massage (no joke) can help.

Author: Vertigo#0439
Content: @Lumbi I went to the emergency room today was the worst pain I ever had specially running through my arm. I Rather be shot than that.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: I have pinched a nerve and herniated a disc in two different incidences.

Author: Vertigo#0439
Content: Does yours hurt like you rather be decapitated with a spoon too?

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: The pinched nerve made my arm and hand go numb a few dozen times throughout the day depending on my posture.  There was not much pain.  The herniated disc was similar with the pins and needles in the hand and arm. But the there was lots of pain. Shooting, aching pain.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: It got to where I couldn‚Äôt sleep more than 3 hours or so a night

Author: Vertigo#0439
Content: Must be a budged disk probably.... This sucks

Author: Vertigo#0439
Content: Electric fire

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: A doctor can prescribe you anti inflamitories and a nerve pain.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: In the mean time, don‚Äôt ‚Äústretch‚Äù anything. I was exacerbating my situation by often stretching my neck which was further inflaming my herniated disc

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: Ice the F out of it.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: Some people like to freeze a water bottle and use it as a neck pillow. That can help put traction pressure on the neck too. Positions that help gently elongate the neck can alleviate some of the pain due to inflammation.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: Go see a doc. I waited until it was nearly unbearable. If you start to lose strength in your arm, that‚Äôs a bad sign.
